Sweet Surprises! Your North Carolina Guide to the Top 5 Halloween Candies This Year

Find the perfect treats for your trick-or-treaters across the Tar Heel State!

By The Bill Layne Insurance Team • October 10, 2025 • Elkin, NC

Halloween is just around the corner, and as the leaves change across our beautiful North Carolina, from the Blue Ridge Mountains to the Outer Banks, one question looms large for every homeowner: "What are the top 5 candy to give on Halloween this year in North Carolina?" Here at Bill Layne Insurance in Elkin, we're not just about protecting your home and auto; we're also about ensuring your Halloween is as sweet and safe as possible! This year, let's make sure your trick-or-treaters in Raleigh, Charlotte, and every small town in between go home with smiles and the very best Halloween candy NC has to offer.

1. Reese's Peanut Butter Cups: The Uncontested Champion

A perfect blend of chocolate and peanut butter, loved by all ages.

You simply can't go wrong with Reese's. These delightful discs of chocolatey peanut butter goodness consistently rank at the top of every candy poll. Whether you're handing out king-sized bars or mini versions, trick-or-treaters across North Carolina, from the bustling streets of Charlotte to the quieter neighborhoods of Elkin, will be thrilled to find these in their bags. They're a reliable crowd-pleaser and truly the best Halloween candy NC can offer.

2. Skittles & M&M's: Colorful Variety for Everyone

Fruity explosions or classic chocolate buttons, offering options for diverse palates.

Offering a mix of Skittles and M&M's ensures you hit every preference. The rainbow of fruity flavors in Skittles brings joy, while M&M's provide that satisfying chocolate crunch. These are especially popular with younger kids and can be a great way to accommodate different tastes. Residents in Raleigh often tell us these are their go-to candy for trick-or-treaters Charlotte and other big cities love, proving their widespread appeal.

3. Snickers & Kit Kat: Satisfying Chocolate Bar Staples

Hearty chocolate bars that provide a substantial, delicious treat.

For those who appreciate a more substantial treat, Snickers and Kit Kat bars are excellent choices. The caramel, nougat, and peanuts of a Snickers, or the crisp wafers of a Kit Kat, are always a hit. These mini-versions are perfect for satisfying hunger after a long night of trick-or-treating around communities near Lake Norman or the Outer Banks. They certainly round out the top 5 candy to give on Halloween this year in North Carolina.

4. Gummy Worms & Bears: Chewy Delights for the Younger Crowd

Fun, fruity, and delightfully chewy – a favorite for many children.

Gummy candies, like worms and bears, are a staple for the younger demographic. Their bright colors and chewy texture make them irresistibly fun. These are fantastic for adding variety to the Halloween treats Elkin and other family-friendly towns across North Carolina cherish. Look for individually wrapped packs to keep them hygienic and easy to distribute.

5. Smarties & Tootsie Rolls: Timeless Classics

Old-school charm and simple sweetness that appeal to all generations.

Sometimes, the simple, classic candies are the most cherished. Smarties, with their chalky sweetness, and Tootsie Rolls, with their unique chewy chocolate flavor, evoke a sense of nostalgia for many adults and offer a different kind of treat for kids. They're often budget-friendly and great for ensuring you have plenty of Halloween candy NC homes need to last the whole evening, especially in high-traffic neighborhoods.

No matter which of these top 5 candy to give on Halloween this year in North Carolina you choose, the most important thing is to have fun and enjoy the community spirit. From our team at Bill Layne Insurance in Elkin, we wish you a spooky, sweet, and safe Halloween!

Frequently Asked Questions

Q: What's the best way to ensure Halloween treats are safe for kids?

Safety tips for distributing and consuming Halloween candy.

A: Always opt for individually wrapped, commercially produced candies. Advise parents to inspect all treats before consumption and discard anything that looks tampered with or unwrapped. For young children, be mindful of choking hazards like hard candies. While this guide focuses on the top 5 candy to give on Halloween this year in North Carolina, remember safety first!

Q: Are there any unique Halloween traditions in North Carolina?

Exploring local Halloween customs and events.

A: North Carolina boasts many unique Halloween festivities! Beyond traditional trick-or-treating in neighborhoods from Asheville to Wilmington, many towns host elaborate fall festivals, corn mazes, and even ghost tours, particularly in historic cities like New Bern. Check local community listings for events happening near you in Elkin or your specific NC town.
